results.name: Decimal expansion of the fractional part of e^e^e^e.
comment: It was conjectured (but remains unproved) that this sequence is infinite and aperiodic.
formula: a(n) = A085667(n+1656521), where 1656521 is the length of the integer part of e^e^e^e.
results.author: _Vladimir Reshetnikov_, Apr 26 2013
